There are two separate notifier options for tint2 in Lilidog.
For the automatic timer version used in a tint2 executable from the 
'plus' symbol in the tint2 panel, see the readme-notifier in 
~/.config/tint2/executors.

All of the necessary files are in the ~/.config/tint2 for either
version of the notification scripts.

For the manual apt update checker, there are two scripts.
~/.config/tint2/scripts/tint-2-apt-update-check  - main script
~/.config/tint2/scripts/tint-2-apt-update-check-color - for icon color
/usr/share/lilidog/tint2/update-options - to call the script
/usr/local/bin/update/notifier - optional use for using nala.

There is an alternate main script available if you would like to remove 
the --listen option allowing the icon to be used in autostart.

Simply rename tint2-apt-update-check to tint2-apt-update-check.bak,
and rename the tint2-apt-update-check-nolisten version to:
tint2-apt-update-check

When changing the notification icon color, you will need to quit and
restart the notification for the color change to take affect.
